    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-11T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-11T15:00:00-05:00" n="219"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/12–1144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-11T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 11, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 11—6:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10997. For attention of Mr. Dunn. Thank you for your 10249, December 7, in reply
                    to the last paragraph of my 10609, December 1.</p>
                <p>The directive on treatment of United Nations POW’s<note n="94" xml:id="d219fn94"
                        >Prisoners of War.</note> in Germany I am sure you realize involves
                    political considerations as well as military action. It therefore clearly falls
                    within the category of directives which we agreed in the conference with the War
                    Department should be considered by the EAC. Both you and McCloy were present at
                    this meeting. My inability to act is holding back the work of the committee
                    authorized by the EAC to consider this subject. The British, the Russians and
                    the French are all ready to proceed. I hope that the differences which you
                    referred to in your message and which you explained would be discussed at a
                    higher level conference scheduled to meet on December 9 have been resolved and
                    that we may expect a reply the early part of this week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
